The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | 3 killed in mishaps
                                                                                                               3 killed in mishaps
          OUR BUREAU                              
	A private bus on route 12C/2 crushed a four-year-old boy near Camp No. 3 on the road leading to New Town from Kestopur on Sunday evening. Ajoy Mistri and his mother were travelling on a relatives cycle, when it was hit from behind by the bus. The two adults were flung to the side of the road. Witnesses said the bus was being driven recklessly over the potholed road. The driver fled. A mob damaged the bus.        
	Chhaya Halder, 75, died on Sunday afternoon after being knocked down by a speeding South Dum Dum Municipality garbage truck near Dum Dum cantonment on Sunday. Chhaya was travelling in a cycle-rickshaw that was hit by the truck.         
	Raj Kumar Ray, 42, was run over by a private bus at the intersection of Strand Road and Fairlie Place on Sunday afternoon while crossing the road. The driver was arrested.                                                                                                                                                                           
